  <front>
    <title>JWK Thumbprint URI</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-ietf-oauth-jwk-thumbprint-uri-00"/>
    <author initials="M." surname="Jones" fullname="Michael Jones">
      <organization>Microsoft</organization>
    </author>
    <author initials="K." surname="Yasuda" fullname="Kristina Yasuda">
      <organization>Microsoft</organization>
    </author>
    <date day="29" month="January" year="2022"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>This specification registers a kind of URI that represents a JSON Web
   Key (JWK) Thumbprint value.  JWK Thumbprints are defined in RFC 7638.
   This enables JWK Thumbprints to be used, for instance, as key
   identifiers in contexts requiring URIs.</t>
    </abstract>
  </front>
